. –
</emphasis>
<collectingCountry id="34FF764B2741120AAB6C3796FE1FFF07" box="[319,431,206,229]" name="Singapore" pageId="8" pageNumber="25">Singapore</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="04F265502741120AAAC73655FEE9FD47" pageId="8" pageNumber="25" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="4C5736DB2741120AAAC73655FEE9FD47" blockId="8.[148,788,269,677]" pageId="8" pageNumber="25">
<emphasis id="7E9CEAC92741120AAAC73655FEA9FEC7" bold="true" box="[148,281,269,293]" pageId="8" pageNumber="25">
<emphasis id="7E9CEAC92741120AAAC73655FF49FEC7" bold="true" box="[148,249,269,293]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="25">Remarks</emphasis>
. –
</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="8BE84D582741120AAB763656FDA8FEC7" authority="Zhang &amp; Yang &amp; Grootaert, 2008" authorityName="Zhang &amp; Yang &amp; Grootaert" authorityYear="2008" box="[293,536,270,293]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Hercostomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="limosus" status="new species">
<emphasis id="7E9CEAC92741120AAB763656FDA8FEC7" box="[293,536,270,293]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="25">Hercostomus limosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel id="65AF57B22741120AA8793656FD07FEC7" box="[554,695,270,293]" pageId="8" pageNumber="25" rank="species">new species</taxonomicNameLabel>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="8BE84D582741120AA8AA3656FEA3FEA7" authority="Zhang &amp; Yang &amp; Grootaert, 2008" authorityName="Zhang &amp; Yang &amp; Grootaert" authorityYear="2008" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Hercostomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lanceolatus" status="new species">
<emphasis id="7E9CEAC92741120AA8AA3656FEA3FEA7" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="25">H. lanceolatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel id="65AF57B22741120AAB763676FE1FFEA7" box="[293,431,302,325]" pageId="8" pageNumber="25" rank="species">new species</taxonomicNameLabel>
, are both similar to 
<taxonomicName id="8BE84D582741120AA8CE3676FE85FE87" authority="Becker, 1922" authorityName="Becker" authorityYear="1922" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Hercostomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="notatus">
<emphasis id="7E9CEAC92741120AA8CE3676FCA3FEA7" box="[669,787,302,325]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="25">H. notatus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="28794B2A2741120AAAC73616FE85FE87" author="Becker, T" box="[148,309,334,357]" pageId="8" pageNumber="25" pagination="1 - 247" refId="ref7585" refString="Becker, T. H., 1922. Dipterologische Studien Dolichopodidae der Indo-Australischen Region. Capita Zoologica, 1: 1 - 247." type="journal article" year="1922">Becker, 1922</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, from 
<collectingCountry id="34FF764B2741120AABD43616FE6CFE87" box="[391,476,334,357]" name="Taiwan" pageId="8" pageNumber="25">Taiwan</collectingCountry>
in having a wing stigma. Examination of a male (Formosa Sauter, Takao 
<date id="3856101B2741120AA8FA3636FCBFFE67" box="[681,783,366,389]" pageId="8" pageNumber="25" value="1907-05-03">1907.V.3</date>
; 
<taxonomicName id="8BE84D582741120AAAC736D6FEB1FE47" authorityName="Becker" authorityYear="1922" box="[148,257,398,421]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Hercostomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="notatus">
<emphasis id="7E9CEAC92741120AAAC736D6FEB1FE47" box="[148,257,398,421]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="25">H. notatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
det. Becker), here designated as 
<typeStatus id="935388792741120AA80736D6FD05FE47" box="[596,693,398,421]" pageId="8" pageNumber="25">lectotype</typeStatus>
revealed that it has R 
<subScript id="D06C349E2741120AAB7036E2FE8BFE2A" attach="left" box="[291,315,442,456]" fontSize="6" pageId="8" pageNumber="25">4+5</subScript>
thickened from its base onwards and the thickening ends halfway the vein i.e. shortly beyond the stigma. 
<figureCitation id="D4D32A5E2741120AAAA236B6FEEFFDE7" box="[241,351,494,517]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="6.[150,194,2078,2099]" captionTargetBox="[152,1475,567,2018]" captionTargetId="figure-155@6.[133,1501,535,2051]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figs. 14–19. Hercostomus lanceolatus, new species, male: 14, antenna; 15, wing; 16, male genitalia; 17, claw-like appendage on aedeagus; 18, ventral lobe of surstyli; 19, dorsal lobe of surstyli." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5339237" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5339237/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="25">
Figure 
<quantity id="8B109B3E2741120AAB1736B6FEEFFDE7" box="[324,351,494,517]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.572" pageId="8" pageNumber="25" unit="in" value="18.0">18</quantity>
</figureCitation>
in 
<bibRefCitation id="28794B2A2741120AABD836B6FD9FFDE7" author="Becker, T" box="[395,559,494,517]" pageId="8" pageNumber="25" pagination="1 - 247" refId="ref7585" refString="Becker, T. H., 1922. Dipterologische Studien Dolichopodidae der Indo-Australischen Region. Capita Zoologica, 1: 1 - 247." type="journal article" year="1922">Becker (1922)</bibRefCitation>
does not show this thickening. Further it should be noted that the stigma is not black as Becker wrote, but also brownish like in both other species. Finally the cercus is set with pale hairs, not black ones and the aedeagus does not bear a denticle like in the other two species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
